to do 800 pages and 100 was just
too short and so I had to leave

00:28:03.860 --> 00:28:05.526
out so many great things.

00:28:05.860 --> 00:28:07.096
I believe it's in the
reading list, but I just had

00:28:07.890 --> 00:28:09.756
to leave out so many things.

00:28:09.890 --> 00:28:11.223
Thank you very much.

00:28:11.890 --> 00:28:12.023
Okay. One more question I think.

00:28:13.890 --> 00:28:14.423
&gt;&gt; Yes. I grew up reading
Mary Poppins.

00:28:15.890 --> 00:28:16.023
&gt;&gt; Anita Silvey: Oh, a good one.

00:28:17.890 --> 00:28:18.623
&gt;&gt; All these stories
from other countries.

00:28:19.890 --> 00:28:20.803
I am also a great aunt to boys
growing up in sports-oriented homes

00:28:23.310 --> 00:28:27.043
as well as academic homes but
sports so it is a challenge

00:28:27.690 --> 00:28:27.710
to not give them what I want
but what they would enjoy.

00:28:31.270 --> 00:28:33.070
&gt;&gt; Anita Silvey: Yes, yeah.

00:28:33.270 --> 00:28:37.203
To remember the mantra is the
right book for the right child

00:28:37.810 --> 00:28:41.010
at the right time and that
is honoring the child.

00:28:41.220 --> 00:28:41.746
That is very important
to do in all reading.

00:28:43.560 --> 00:28:46.026
We honor who they are
as human beings.

00:28:46.580 --> 00:28:47.646
Okay. Thank you.

00:28:49.390 --> 00:28:50.590
One more question.

00:28:51.390 --> 00:28:53.056
I think we have one more.

00:28:53.390 --> 00:28:54.390
Quick one.

00:28:55.390 --> 00:28:55.990
&gt;&gt; Hi. I was wondering
I have a question

00:28:57.390 --> 00:28:59.460
about what your advice would be
for inspirational writers who would

00:28:59.720 --> 00:28:59.893
like to pursue writing as their job

00:29:01.880 --> 00:29:02.010
but considering how
what the competition is

00:29:04.550 --> 00:29:06.483
for trying to publish a book.

00:29:06.610 --> 00:29:08.076
&gt;&gt; Anita Silvey: Yeah.

00:29:08.610 --> 00:29:10.743
One of the things that I say to
all writers write what you have

00:29:10.610 --> 00:29:11.183
to write, look every now and
then at what's published,

00:29:13.570 --> 00:29:15.503
but don't get consumed by it.

00:29:16.440 --> 00:29:16.736
Find your own voice, find what
you have to say, keep going,

00:29:20.010 --> 00:29:24.210
perseverance is everything okay
so just keep doing it and don't,

00:29:24.970 --> 00:29:25.436
there's that voice
that's always going

00:29:26.970 --> 00:29:27.503
to say they don't need my book,
they don't need me, I have nothing

00:29:30.770 --> 00:29:30.853
to say, I am insane, in fact,
to be doing this in my pajamas

00:29:34.620 --> 00:29:35.223
at whatever hour, 3 in the morning,
okay, that voice is always there.

00:29:38.550 --> 00:29:39.146
Don't give in to it, keep
writing what you need

00:29:41.020 --> 00:29:45.153
to because you know what I finally
realized is I could do books

00:29:45.670 --> 00:29:48.670
about what I loved, which
was children's books

00:29:48.670 --> 00:29:48.800
that had never occurred
to me so just keep going.

00:29:51.740 --> 00:29:53.340
That's always my advice.

00:29:53.740 --> 00:29:54.740
Keep going.

00:29:55.740 --> 00:29:56.740
Thank you all.

